commit.message:
Replace custom cue file parsing with libcue (#29)

The old implementation for cue file parsing did not attempt to adhere to spec.
This meant  many cue files would simply not parse correctly and therefore
would not create the intended track breaks.

Replacing said parsing with a more robust library designed for parsing cue files fixes
many, if not all, of the parsing bugs thusfar discovered.
